cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.PL 

This paper proposes a hardware-based in-process isolation system to prevent vulnerabilities caused by out-of-bound memory accesses. As such, it is likely to fall under the categories of computer security (cs.CR), computer architecture (cs.AR), software engineering (cs.SE), systems and control (cs.SY), and programming languages (cs.PL).
